title: Bearcats picked fifth in America East preseason poll
text:
Bearcats picked fifth in America East preseason poll 
By wbng sports Bearcats picked fifth in America East preseason poll October 22, 2015 Updated Oct 22, 2015 at 8:46 PM EDT 
(WBNG Binghamton) With a number of returning pieces, expectations are growing for the Binghamton University men's basketball program. But for the second year in a row the America East coaches feel like the Bearcats are just a middle-of-the-pack team. 
BU was picked fifth in the America East preseason coaches' poll that was released on Thursday. 
WBNG E-News - Sign Up For Our Newsletter! 
The Bearcats come in behind Stony Brook, Albany, Vermont and New Hampshire. 
It's the second year in a row that they have been picked to finish fifth in the conference. 
At the top, the SeaWolves are the overwhelming favorite to win the conference, receiving seven of the possible eight first place votes. 
Binghamton will get its shot at them right away. BU opens the conference season by hosting Stony Brook on Jan. 6. 
2015-16 Men's Basketball Preseason Coaches' Poll 1. Stony Brook (7 1st place votes), 63 pts.2. Albany (2), 55
